OL,3,CJD Vance tells UK anti-immigration
OL,4,Cprotesters 'it's OK to defend your
OL,5,Cculture'
OL,7,FUS Vice President JD Vance has told
OL,8,FBritish anti-immigration protesters it
OL,9,Fis "OK to defend your culture",
OL,10,Frejecting claims that tighter border
OL,11,Fcontrols are racist.
OL,13,FAsked by a reporter to comment on last
OL,14,Fweekend's Unite the Kingdom march in
OL,15,Fcentral London, organised by far-right
OL,16,Factivist Tommy Robinson, whose real
OL,17,Fname is Stephen Yaxley-Lennon, the
OL,18,FRepublican politician said it was
OL,19,Freasonable for people "to want to
OL,20,Fcontrol who comes into their country"
OL,21,Fand urged them to "keep on going".
OL,26,@qD@DOUqD@^O]|D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
